      <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none text-gray-600 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
        <p>If you are a homeowner in Fort Lauderdale considering a roof replacement, one of the first questions you likely have is about cost. The price of a new roof depends on several factors, including the size of your home, the materials you choose, and the complexity of the installation. In this guide, we break down the typical costs you can expect in 2025.</p>

        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-8 mb-4">Average Roof Replacement Costs in Fort Lauderdale</h2>
        <p>For a standard single-family home in Fort Lauderdale (approximately 1,500 to 2,500 square feet of roof area), you can expect to pay between $8,000 and $30,000 for a full roof replacement. The wide range reflects the variety of materials and project requirements. Asphalt shingle roofs fall on the lower end, while <a href="/service/tile-roofing" class="text-accent hover:underline">tile roofing</a> and <a href="/service/metal-roofing" class="text-accent hover:underline">metal roofing</a> systems cost more but offer superior longevity and wind resistance.</p>

        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-8 mb-4">Cost by Roofing Material</h2>
        <p>Here is a general breakdown of costs per square foot installed in the Fort Lauderdale area:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Asphalt Shingles:</strong> $3.50 - $5.50 per sq ft — the most popular and affordable option for <a href="/service/residential-roofing" class="text-accent hover:underline">residential roofing</a>.</li>
          <li><strong>Metal Roofing:</strong> $7.00 - $14.00 per sq ft — excellent durability and energy efficiency, ideal for hurricane-prone areas.</li>
          <li><strong>Tile Roofing:</strong> $8.00 - $16.00 per sq ft — long-lasting and aesthetically appealing, a classic choice in South Florida.</li>
          <li><strong>Copper Roofing:</strong> $15.00 - $25.00+ per sq ft — premium material with exceptional lifespan and distinctive appearance. Learn more about our <a href="/service/copper-roofing" class="text-accent hover:underline">copper roofing services</a>.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-8 mb-4">Factors That Affect Your Roof Replacement Cost</h2>
        <p>Several variables influence the final price of your roof replacement project:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Roof size and pitch:</strong> Steeper roofs require more labor and safety equipment.</li>
          <li><strong>Material selection:</strong> Premium materials cost more upfront but save money on maintenance over time.</li>
          <li><strong>Removal of old roof:</strong> Tear-off and disposal of existing roofing adds to the total cost.</li>
          <li><strong>Permits and inspections:</strong> Broward County requires building permits for roof replacements.</li>
          <li><strong>Structural repairs:</strong> Damaged decking or fascia boards increase the project scope.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-8 mb-4">How to Get the Best Value</h2>
        <p>To ensure you get a fair price and quality workmanship, always get multiple estimates from licensed, insured contractors. Look for companies with strong Google reviews and local experience. At JDM Roofing, we provide free, detailed estimates with no hidden fees. Our team has completed over 500 roofing projects across Fort Lauderdale, Miami, and Orlando.</p>

        <p>Investing in quality materials and professional installation protects your home and can increase your property value. <a href="/service/roof-coatings" class="text-accent hover:underline">Roof coatings</a> and regular <a href="/service/roof-maintenance" class="text-accent hover:underline">roof maintenance</a> can also extend the life of your new roof by years.</p>

